      "outcome": "The Silent Spire Keepers, having monitored the Signal-House Families' expanding technological reach through their new perimeter sentinels, are receptive to the proposal. The Keepers' cipher scripture interpreters recognize that the Council's liturgical authority could provide a defensive layer their acoustic jamming alone cannot sustain indefinitely. After three days of deliberation at the neutral waypoint, the Keepers agree in principle to joint stewardship — but impose strict conditions: (1) no more than two shrine auditors may be stationed at the Spire at any time, (2) the Council must publicly excommunicate any operator who installs signal equipment within the Spire's waters, and (3) the Keepers retain sole interpretive authority over the Unspoken Tongue. The Council accepts all conditions. A formal consecration ceremony is scheduled for the next new moon — just before high-water season begins. The Council has secured its first territorial foothold: a permanent (if constrained) presence at the Silent Spire, establishing sole liturgical jurisdiction over its transmissions. However, the agreement remains secret — both parties fear that public knowledge would provoke the Signal-House Families into aggressive countermeasures before the consecration is complete.",
