      "outcome": "The Lacquer Seal Verification Authority establishes a permanent verification station at the Night Courier Depot, staffed by six senior lacquer artificers. The free introductory validation period attracts 78% of all Depot-routed messages within two weeks, as couriers and operators recognize the value of quadruple-authenticated transit for high-value shipments. The Signal-House Families formally endorse the station as their preferred authentication partner, and the Depot's routing ledger now flags non-authenticated messages as \"unverified\" — a soft but effective pressure on operators to adopt the Authority's standard. The Authority's authentication monopoly is no longer forming — it is operational, at least within the Depot's jurisdiction. However, the Shrine Auditors' Council, learning of the station through their remaining Canal Market District informants, issues a private warning to the Signal-House Families that the Authority's templates remain \"consecrated property\" and any commercial use may trigger liturgical sanctions. The Families acknowledge the warning but take no action, calculating that the Council's attention remains fixed on the Silent Spire.",
